Package tage.shapes

Classes for the various object shapes supported by TAGE.
Author:
Scott Gordon
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AnimatedShape
    AnimatedShape contains functions for loading animated models, building animated shapes and their skeletons, and applying animations to the models at runtime.
    AnimatedSkeleton
    A Skeleton describes the hierarchy and structure of any number of bones.
    Animation
    An Animation describes a sequence of frames that can be applied to an AnimatedSkeleton object.
    Cube
    A Cube has 36 vertices, winding order CW, and texture coordinate from (0,0) to (1,1) on each side.
    ImportedModel
    Supports importing OBJ model files into the game.
    Line
    Draws a line segment connecting two specified start and end locations.
    ManualObject
    Abstract class for user-defined manual objects.
    Plane
    Plane is a rectangular object located on the XZ plane.
    RoomBox
    The vertices are the same as for the Cube, but with texture coordinates that align with a single-image, 6-square cubemap texture.
    SkyBoxShape
    The GameEngine instantiates one SkyBox object, there should be no reason for the game application to call the constructor for this class.
    Sphere
    Sphere is described in Chapter 6 of Computer Graphics Programming in OpenGL with Java.
    TerrainPlane
    TerrainPlane is a plane with a large number of vertices, intended for height mapping.
    Torus
    Torus is described in Chapter 6 of Computer Graphics Programming in OpenGL with Java.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    AnimatedShape.EndType
    Specifies what happens when reaching the end of an animation.
